<figure class="architecture-figure" aria-labelledby="architecture-map-title">
  <figcaption id="architecture-map-title">Current shipped architecture: local process, local database</figcaption>
  <div class="architecture-map">
    <div class="node client">
      <strong>Editor or AI client</strong>
      <span>MCP (stdio or HTTP)</span>
    </div>
    <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
    <div class="node daemon">
      <strong>ChunkHound process</strong>
      <span>CLI or per-project daemon · local IPC when shared</span>
    </div>
    <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
    <div class="node database">
      <strong>Project database</strong>
      <span>Local DuckDB or LanceDB · local incremental indexing</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <p class="figure-note">
    Embedding, reranking, and LLM providers may be local or remote. They are provider
    dependencies, not a central ChunkHound query service.
  </p>
</figure>

